{
  "stem": "13874.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- --took the prisoners right as they were captured, even before they were processed, and found-- tried to find out all the tactical information they had, which was who were they, what was in front of us, how-- just basically what is facing us, our line-- so strategical aspect they were us interrogated.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were-- that was handled in the prisoner of war camps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was in the-- at the front line.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was with the troops.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And even before the prisoner of war were turned over to the military police and to the-- the guards, I interrogated them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was the first one they actually saw and talked to.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "German soldiers-- mostly infantrymen-- who were captured at the front-- some who were actually captured-- some who liked to be captured.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I wanted to make sure-- what my-- was our job in our team-- it was a two-man team-- to find out as much as possible, as fast as possible, so that it could be used tactically against them.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were usually very talkative, and basically, they actually helped us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Germans helped us with their brutality.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In one case, I only had to indicate that I knew how to treat them, because I was a former inmate of Dachau; that they did everything and anything just to please me so I didn't get angry at them.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they talk quite freely.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So big question, actually, was to ask the right questions.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That-- that you cannot get from a book.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You have to look at the guy, have to figure out what can he know?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because once a prisoner get accustomed, or get-- to say, I don't know, and get away with, he will use it more and more all the time.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
